22
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:49,610
-根本没道理  -投票率很低
- It doesn't make any sense. - Turnout's bad.

23
00:03:49,610 --> 00:03:52,670
我听说政治新闻网更重关注康威一方
I hear at Politico, they're concentrating mostly on Conway art.

24
00:03:53,470 --> 00:03:55,130
闭嘴  不然就开除你
Shut up or you're fired.

25
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,350
...赛区对手
...division rivals.

26
00:03:57,350 --> 00:03:59,280
这场斗殴很有看点
The fighting was quite a spectacle

27
00:03:59,290 --> 00:04:01,770
但对冰球迷来说  不幸的是
but, unfortunately for hockey fans,

28
00:04:01,770 --> 00:04:03,540
那是昨晚比赛中
that was just about the only action

29
00:04:03,550 --> 00:04:06,000
唯一的看点
to be seen in last night's game.

30
00:04:06,550 --> 00:04:08,440
威尔  马克来了
Will, Mark's here.

31
00:04:10,140 --> 00:04:11,600
希望你睡了会儿
Hope you got some sleep.

32
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:13,320
其实没有
No, not really.

33
00:04:13,990 --> 00:04:15,960
甚至跑了步  但...
Even went for a run, but...

34
00:04:16,740 --> 00:04:17,820
你饿吗
You hungry?

35
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,000
我只是想在今天
Um, I just wanted to connect

36
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,030
接下来的活动前  告诉你一下
before the rest of this day kicks in.

37
00:04:22,510 --> 00:04:23,650
我跟马歇尔谈过了
I spoke to Marshall.

38
00:04:23,650 --> 00:04:25,060
我告诉他了
No, I told him.

39
00:04:25,330 --> 00:04:26,870
情势很喜人
Things are looking good.

40
00:04:27,900 --> 00:04:29,190
非常喜人
Very good.

41
00:04:29,420 --> 00:04:32,190
我很想感谢你做的一切  那支广告还有...
I really want to thank you for everything. I mean, the ad and--

42
00:04:32,190 --> 00:04:33,500
那支广告和我无关
I had nothing to do with that ad.

43
00:04:33,500 --> 00:04:35,530
当然  但...
No, of course, but...

44
00:04:35,530 --> 00:04:37,460
谢谢你的支持
to thank you for your support.

45
00:04:37,460 --> 00:04:38,700
全靠你自己
This is all you.

46
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:40,730
听着
Listen...

47
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:45,440
我...不想说错话
I'm... choosing my words very carefully here.

48
00:04:46,850 --> 00:04:48,100
你得准备好
You need to get ready.

49
00:04:48,450 --> 00:04:49,790
今天会大获全胜
Today's gonna be a good day.

50
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:51,860
你可以等进白宫再睡
You can sleep when you get to the White House.

51
00:04:52,660 --> 00:04:53,770
但也未必
Or maybe not.

52
00:04:55,870 --> 00:04:58,220
准备好吧  威尔  再见
Get yourself together, Will. I'll see you in a bit.

53
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:08,910
你准备好
Are you ready...

54
00:05:15,940 --> 00:05:17,200
来"抓"我了吗
to catch me?

55
00:05:25,450 --> 00:05:28,580
道格  莉安  你们有空吗
Doug, LeAnn... do you have a moment?

56
00:05:40,890 --> 00:05:42,570
从山麓酒店现场发来的报道
Reporting live from the Piedmont Hotel,

57
00:05:42,570 --> 00:05:44,750
现场气氛很激烈
the excitement is definitely in the air right now.

58
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:47,490
最好别让他们看到你证件上的名字
Better not let them see the name on your credentials.

59
00:05:48,090 --> 00:05:50,090
那些人很爱戴他们的总统
Those folks out there love their president.

60
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:52,390
我很爱磅蛋糕
I love pound cake.

61
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,700
不代表它对我有益
Doesn't mean it's good for me.

62
00:05:55,310 --> 00:05:56,730
你怎么样  赛斯
How are you doing, Seth?

63
00:05:58,250 --> 00:06:00,990
-你这里还有粉底没抹匀  -天啊
- You got some foundation right here. - Oh, jeez.

64
00:06:02,650 --> 00:06:04,980
我们还把这称为新闻
And we call it the news.

65
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:06,750
我要做实况报道
I'm doing commentary.

66
00:06:06,790 --> 00:06:09,380
那么迟早会有人问我
Which means eventually someone gets to ask me

67
00:06:09,380 --> 00:06:11,900
我的文章有没有影响到总统的败选
if my articles affected the president's loss.

68
00:06:12,490 --> 00:06:14,420
或胜选
Or his win.

69
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:18,920
祝你顺顺利利  赛斯
I wish you the best, Seth.

70
00:06:19,700 --> 00:06:21,040
你还会找到工作的
You'll land somewhere.

71
00:06:21,630 --> 00:06:22,800
你就是那种人
You're that type.

72
00:06:24,270 --> 00:06:26,390
我们今晚会十分成功
We're going to have a great night tonight.

73
00:06:27,060 --> 00:06:28,770
你没必要哄我
You don't have to spin me.

74
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:31,260
我应该怎么说
How shall I say this?

75
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:36,460
我单身时  总是去败选者的派对
When I was single, I always picked the loser's party.

76
00:06:37,380 --> 00:06:39,900
我在鲍勃·多尔的宴会厅认识了
I met the last Mrs. Hammerschmidt drowning in tequila shots

77
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,870
正豪饮龙舌兰的上任太太
at the Bob Dole ballroom.

78
00:06:42,310 --> 00:06:45,430
而我现在...又单身了
And here I am... single again.

79
00:07:02,020 --> 00:07:04,240
-你现在不在德州了  -道格  省省吧
- You're not in Texas anymore. - Doug, please.

80
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:05,840
-怎么了  -别以为你了解我
- Please what? - Don't think you know me.

81
00:07:05,840 --> 00:07:07,080
我只是想确定你准备好...
Look, I just want to be sure that you're ready for--

82
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:09,000
麦卡伦会做他该做的事
Macallan will do what he has to.

83
00:07:10,940 --> 00:07:12,250
我喜欢赢
I like to win.

84
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:15,380
奖杯  奖牌  焦灼的比赛  我都想赢
Trophies, medals, staring contests. You name it.

85
00:07:15,380 --> 00:07:17,520
你能懂这一点  就能懂我
You understand that, you understand me.

86
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,960
大家好
Hello, everyone.

87
00:07:27,220 --> 00:07:28,890
现在为时尚早
Well, it's still early.

88
00:07:29,090 --> 00:07:31,470
今天的大选进程还远远没结束
There's a lot more election to be had today.

89
00:07:31,470 --> 00:07:33,570
我们只是想道个歉
And we just want to apologize that,

90
00:07:33,570 --> 00:07:35,070
因为我们还有点工作要做
because we have a little more work to do,

91
00:07:35,070 --> 00:07:36,550
我们没法早点
we're not gonna be able to get over to the ballroom

92
00:07:36,550 --> 00:07:37,820
抵达宴会厅了
as early as we would like to.

93
00:07:37,820 --> 00:07:39,020
但等我们到了那里
But once we do get there,

94
00:07:39,020 --> 00:07:42,200
我们就会跟你们每一位握手
we are going to shake the hand of each and every one of you,

95
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:44,530
感谢你们为我们所做的
to thank you for all the extraordinary work

96
00:07:44,530 --> 00:07:46,020
出色工作
that you've done for us.

97
00:07:46,580 --> 00:07:49,230
没错  为大家鼓掌吧
That's right, a round of applause all the way around.

98
00:07:51,990 --> 00:07:54,550
我们等会儿派对上见
And we'll see you all at the party a little later.

99
00:08:38,980 --> 00:08:39,890
好点了吗
Better?

100
00:08:40,550 --> 00:08:42,770
嗯  好了一点
Yeah, a little.

101
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:47,170
我第一次上了一位总统
First time I've fucked a president.

102
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:50,470
-不要这样讲  -马歇尔说...
- Oh, don't say that. - Marshall said...

103
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:53,130
我还不是总统
I'm not a president yet.

104
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:54,940
就快了
Almost.

105
00:09:04,180 --> 00:09:05,800
我得穿好衣服
I got to put on a suit.

106
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:08,690
-大家就要来了  -威尔
- People will be here soon. - Will...

107
00:09:11,010 --> 00:09:13,160
你就不能允许自己感受一下吗
can't you let yourself feel it?

108
00:09:23,540 --> 00:09:24,890
就快了
Almost.

109
00:09:30,550 --> 00:09:32,920
-您准备好就开始  先生  -请接通州长
- Ready when you are, sir. - Put the governor on, please.

110
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:34,790
-你好  -米切  我是总统
- Hello. - Mitch, this is the president.

111
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:36,420
我知道你听过简报了
I understand you've been briefed.

112
00:09:36,420 --> 00:09:37,710
总统先生
Oh, Mr. President...

113
00:09:38,010 --> 00:09:40,410
这让我们猝不及防
this is catching us all off guard over here.

114
00:09:40,410 --> 00:09:43,050
州的  当地的  我们都不知道
State, local, we had no idea.

115
00:09:43,050 --> 00:09:44,070
我理解
I understand.

116
00:09:44,070 --> 00:09:46,310
我跟副总统  和国务卿杜兰特在一起
I'm with the vice president, the Secretary of State Durant,

117
00:09:46,310 --> 00:09:49,450
反恐处助理局长格林也在线上
and on the line with us is Counterterrorism Director Green.

118
00:09:49,450 --> 00:09:52,300
州长  很抱歉  但我们必须行动
Governor, sir, I'm sorry, but we needed to act.

119
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:55,120
我直接联系了当地执法部门
I contacted local law enforcement directly.

120
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,830
我是过了好一会儿才知道
Well, it took a while to get to me.

121
00:09:56,830 --> 00:09:58,980
米切  反恐处助理局长要与我们分享一些
Mitch, the Counterterrorism Director will be sharing information

122
00:09:58,980 --> 00:10:00,580
绝不能外泄的信息
that we must keep amongst ourselves.

123
00:10:00,590 --> 00:10:04,680
我们不想做任何会影响今天投票的事
We do not want to do anything that affects today's voting.

124
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:05,870
45分钟之前
Forty-five minutes ago,

125
00:10:05,870 --> 00:10:08,590
我们突袭了穆罕默德·卡拉比的住处  先生
we raided the home of Muhammed Kalabi, sir.

126
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,010
在戴德里克大街
On Deaderick Ave.

127
00:10:10,020 --> 00:10:12,570
-嗯  -那里离体育场很近
- Yes. - It's near the Coliseum.

128
00:10:12,810 --> 00:10:14,490
嫌疑人不在公寓里
The suspect was not in his apartment,

129
00:10:14,490 --> 00:10:17,000
但是我们发现了制造炸弹的材料
but we did find bomb-making material.

130
00:10:19,610 --> 00:10:21,970
-天哪  -米切
- Jesus, uh... - Now, Mitch...

131
00:10:21,970 --> 00:10:24,570
我们最不希望的就是让你恐慌
the last thing we want is for you to panic.

132
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:27,590
你一定要知道联邦政府
You must know that you have the full support

133
00:10:27,590 --> 00:10:29,150
会全力支持你
of the federal government here.

134
00:10:29,150 --> 00:10:32,090
接下来怎么办
Um, it... Well, what... what's next?

135
00:10:32,090 --> 00:10:35,440
我们相信他的目标是某个投票中心
We believe his target is one of the voting centers.

136
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:36,880
我们知道你已经安排了警卫队
We know you have soldiers in place,

137
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:38,530
采取了安全措施  设置了检查站
security measures and checkpoints.

138
00:10:38,530 --> 00:10:40,220
格林局长正赶去见你
Director Green is on his way to you.

139
00:10:40,220 --> 00:10:43,210
联调局诺克斯维尔办事处会设立指挥中心
There will be a command center out of the FBI office in Knoxville

140
00:10:43,210 --> 00:10:44,210
我们将进行协调
where we will coordinate.

141
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:46,840
我的家人今早就在体育场投了票
My family voted at the Coliseum this morning.

142
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:48,100
米切  听我说
Mitch, listen to me.

143
00:10:48,450 --> 00:10:51,360
不管你需要什么  我们都会提供
Whatever you need, we will provide.

144
00:10:54,450 --> 00:10:55,990
俄亥俄的数字怎么样
How are the Ohio numbers?

145
00:10:55,990 --> 00:10:58,120
投票率这么低  不好估计
It's hard to gauge with turnout this low.

146
00:10:58,130 --> 00:10:59,470
就是要这效果
That was kind of the point.

147
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:01,860
是对于另一方  不是民主党
For the other side, not Democrats.

148
00:11:01,860 --> 00:11:04,300
州长担心了  你有什么数据吗
The governor's worried. Do you have any numbers?

149
00:11:04,410 --> 00:11:05,950
没有  只有我们给过你的
No, just what we gave you.

150
00:11:05,950 --> 00:11:07,290
我以为总统可能有
I would think that the president might have

151
00:11:07,290 --> 00:11:09,800
我们接触不到的数据
access to some numbers that we don't.

152
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:11,580
如果我有  你也会有
When I get them, you'll get them.

153
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,700
-我们很担心  -坚持住
- We're worried. - Hang in there.

154
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:16,370
等过了3点这一波我再跟你联系
I'll touch base with you after the three o'clock wave.

155
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:20,200
请让我单独待会儿  谢谢
If you could all just give me a moment, please. Thank you.

156
00:11:20,950 --> 00:11:22,270
你最好去宴会厅
You better head over to the ballroom.

157
00:11:22,270 --> 00:11:24,070
我们其中一人应该到场
One of us should make an appearance.

158
00:11:24,340 --> 00:11:26,230
先生  这一天终于到了
Sir, the day has finally arrived.

159
00:11:26,230 --> 00:11:29,550
是啊  让我们看看这一天有多长吧
Yes, and let's see just how long this day lasts.

160
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:36,590
想像一下国安局给我打电话问
Imagine my surprise when the NSA called me

161
00:11:36,590 --> 00:11:38,860
穆罕默德·卡拉比的事时我有多惊讶吧
about Muhammed Kalabi just...

162
00:11:39,220 --> 00:11:41,350
你的电话随后就到
moments before you did.

163
00:11:42,130 --> 00:11:44,180
情况还在发展
Situation is still unfolding.

164
00:11:44,190 --> 00:11:45,770
在选举日
On Election Day?

165
00:11:51,330 --> 00:11:52,340
弗兰西斯
Francis...

166
00:11:53,450 --> 00:11:56,040
跟你共事真是一段独特的经历
it's been quite a journey working with you.

167
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:01,450
卡拉比溜进了国内
Kalabi slipped into the country,

168
00:12:01,450 --> 00:12:03,590
他正策划着一起针对
and he's planning a terrorist attack

169
00:12:03,590 --> 00:12:06,340
田纳西某个投票中心的恐怖袭击
against a voting center in Tennessee.

170
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:10,280
这种说法太吓人了
And that is a terrifying proposition.

171
00:12:11,190 --> 00:12:12,360
我需要你在白宫
Well, I may need you to stay around

172
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:14,180
再多待一阵  凯茜
the White House a bit longer, Cathy,

173
00:12:14,180 --> 00:12:16,880
直到事态平息
until this situation is resolved.

174
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,720
好的
Of course.

175
00:12:20,820 --> 00:12:22,340
我只是说
I was only saying...

176
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:25,290
这一路以来很不错了
it's been a good run.

177
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:41,030
说得像她能激怒我似的
As if she could ever get under my skin.

178
00:12:41,390 --> 00:12:43,720
我现在还不用去宴会
I don't need to get to the party just yet.

179
00:12:43,990 --> 00:12:47,670
人们伸着汗涔涔的手想要最后一次向我致敬
Sweaty palms, eager to pay me their last respects.

180
00:12:47,670 --> 00:12:50,130
但他们真正想用的致敬方式
When what they really want to do to show their respect

181
00:12:50,140 --> 00:12:51,970
是把所有子弹都射向我
is to empty their bullets in my body,

182
00:12:51,970 --> 00:12:54,060
