Unacceptable. Find Kalabi.

357
00:21:13,660 --> 00:21:14,930
州长不会希望
The governor does not wanna

358
00:21:14,930 --> 00:21:17,480
在这么晚的时候颁发宵禁令
have to institute a curfew this late in the game.

359
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:19,930
-米切  -是  先生
- And, Mitch... - Uh, yes, sir.

360
00:21:19,930 --> 00:21:22,690
你不能关闭投票
...you are not closing the polls.

361
00:21:34,840 --> 00:21:36,200
你觉得我们该关吗
You think we should?

362
00:21:37,270 --> 00:21:38,920
我没法发表意见
I can't weigh in on this.

363
00:21:59,170 --> 00:22:00,760
我得跟肖娜谈谈
I need to talk to Shawna.

364
00:22:03,980 --> 00:22:06,760
公众还要承受多少丑闻
How many scandals should the public be expected to endure

365
00:22:05,900 --> 00:22:08,360
{\an1}{\pos(165.6,221.85)}汤姆·汉默施密特
《华盛顿先驱报》

366
00:22:06,760 --> 00:22:08,560
才会说"够了"
before they say, "Enough"?

367
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:10,800
会说"我不出门了"
Before they say, "I'm staying home"?

368
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:14,210
会对国家完全丧失信心
Before they lose complete faith in this democratic republic?

369
00:22:14,210 --> 00:22:16,520
上次出现这样的趋势
This is a trend that dates back at least

370
00:22:16,520 --> 00:22:18,720
是尼克松躲过牢狱之灾的时候
to when Nixon avoided jail time.

371
00:22:19,340 --> 00:22:20,560
好了  结束
Okay, we're out.

372
00:22:28,150 --> 00:22:30,750
-真不错  -我不需要粉丝  肖恩
- You're good. - I don't need fans, Sean.

373
00:22:30,750 --> 00:22:32,740
只是真诚的欣赏
Just genuine appreciation.

374
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:36,020
喝一杯吗  一杯是酒  一杯不是
Would you like a drink? One is brown and one is not.

375
00:22:36,230 --> 00:22:38,440
-今晚会很漫长  -我听说不是
- It's gonna be a long night. - That's not what I hear.

376
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:40,430
那么  田纳西
So, Tennessee...

377
00:22:40,430 --> 00:22:41,560
是问题所在
Is the question.

378
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:42,560
怎么样
And?

379
00:22:42,720 --> 00:22:44,010
我的男伴什么都不知道
My date knew nothing.

380
00:22:44,270 --> 00:22:45,600
你在到处问了吗
Are you making the rounds?

381
00:22:45,700 --> 00:22:47,640
这里的人比我一般接触的年龄要大
Crowd's a little older than I'm used to, but...

382
00:22:47,870 --> 00:22:51,960
但是  没错  他们话多  却没什么料
yes, they're a talkative bunch... that don't say much.

383
00:22:53,320 --> 00:22:54,420
我要酒
I'll take the brown one.

384
00:22:56,510 --> 00:22:59,710
那是帕特里夏·惠特克  民主党全国委员会主席
That's Patricia Whittaker over there. Chairperson of the DNC.

385
00:22:59,710 --> 00:23:01,220
她有次在奥马哈一家酒吧里扇了我个耳光
She slapped me once in a bar in Omaha.

386
00:23:01,220 --> 00:23:02,750
我也不知道为什么
For the life of me, I can't tell you why.

387
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:09,600
田纳西州有问题
There's something wrong with Tennessee.

388
00:23:10,870 --> 00:23:12,950
你的男伴要么在撒谎  要么在抵赖
Your date is either lying or denying.

389
00:23:34,870 --> 00:23:37,490
这是什么意思
What did you mean by this?

390
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:40,250
演讲背后的字
On the back of the speech?

391
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:45,240
没事  别提了
Nothing. Forget it.

392
00:23:48,460 --> 00:23:49,970
"还有时间"
"There's still time"?

393
00:23:52,060 --> 00:23:53,620
还有时间做什么
There's still time for what?

394
00:23:57,150 --> 00:23:58,200
你在干什么
What are you doing?

395
00:23:59,730 --> 00:24:00,990
你和你丈夫
You and your husband.

396
00:24:02,010 --> 00:24:04,020
准备赢得选举
Getting ready to win an election.

397
00:24:05,290 --> 00:24:07,030
我看到你的样子了
I see the way you're acting.

398
00:24:18,750 --> 00:24:23,180
你知道我们今天打算赢得选举吗
Do you realize we have every intention of winning today?

399
00:24:24,450 --> 00:24:25,220
当然
Sure.

400
00:24:27,500 --> 00:24:28,620
但然后呢
But then what?

401
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:49,310
我以前会去缅因州的一间小木屋
I used to go to this cabin... up in Maine.

402
00:24:51,620 --> 00:24:53,880
窗户关不严实
The windows don't close properly.

403
00:24:55,940 --> 00:24:59,460
整个夏天都能闻到大海的气味儿
You can smell the ocean all summer long.

404
00:25:16,330 --> 00:25:18,840
我觉得你还是去宴会厅吧
I do think it's better you go to the ballroom.

405
00:25:32,390 --> 00:25:36,850
如果你尚未投票  我保证  你会有机会的
If you have not voted, I assure you, you will get the chance.

406
00:25:36,860 --> 00:25:39,490
但出于良心
But I cannot, in good conscience,

407
00:25:39,490 --> 00:25:44,130
我不能在确保安全前  允许投票继续
allow balloting to continue until I am satisfied that it is safe.

408
00:25:44,130 --> 00:25:46,690
为此  随着夜晚将至
To that end, as nightfall approaches,

409
00:25:46,690 --> 00:25:48,640
我要宣布今晚
I am announcing an enforced,

410
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:51,940
执行全州宵禁
state-wide curfew, effective tonight.

411
00:25:52,080 --> 00:25:56,100
如果你中部时间晚8点30还未回家
If you are not in your home by 8:30 p.m. central time,

412
00:25:56,100 --> 00:25:59,770
或是东部时间9点30
or by 9:30 in the eastern parts of this state,

413
00:25:59,770 --> 00:26:04,030
你将被拘禁甚至逮捕
you will be subject to detention and possible arrest.

414
00:26:04,030 --> 00:26:05,540
这是怎么回事
What the hell's going on?

415
00:26:05,540 --> 00:26:08,300
我们会赢下宾州和俄亥俄州  就这么回事
What's going on is we're gonna win Pennsylvania and Ohio.

416
00:26:08,690 --> 00:26:10,300
那么你就超过270了
That puts you over 270.

417
00:26:10,300 --> 00:26:12,250
投票还在继续  大家还在投票
The polls are still open. People are still voting.

418
00:26:12,250 --> 00:26:13,780
我的直觉是那些票属于我们
My gut says they're ours.

419
00:26:13,850 --> 00:26:16,370
没有田纳西也272了
That's 272 without Tennessee.

420
00:26:16,370 --> 00:26:18,210
那混蛋暂停了投票
That asshole's suspending the vote.

421
00:26:18,210 --> 00:26:20,810
那得由他的州务卿决定  她是我们的人
That's up to his secretary of state, and she's on our side.

422
00:26:20,810 --> 00:26:23,060
-都这样了她还有的选吗  -州长  听我说
- She's gonna have a choice after this? - Governor, listen to me.

423
00:26:23,060 --> 00:26:24,330
我们还要让弗兰西斯·安德伍德
I mean, how long do we let Francis Underwood

424
00:26:24,340 --> 00:26:26,640
耍这种手段多久啊
get away with this kind of shit? Huh? How long?

425
00:26:26,650 --> 00:26:28,200
他不会得逞的
He won't get away with it.

426
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:29,160
不会的
He won't.

427
00:26:29,270 --> 00:26:31,230
刚刚是田纳西州长
That was Tennessee governor...

428
00:26:31,230 --> 00:26:31,950
相信我
Trust me.

429
00:26:31,950 --> 00:26:33,870
宣布全州宵禁
...announcing a state-wide curfew.

430
00:26:34,330 --> 00:26:35,520
扯淡
Bullshit.

431
00:26:36,940 --> 00:26:39,710
全州的投票中心都在关闭
Voting centers all across the state are being shut down,

432
00:26:39,710 --> 00:26:43,100
中部时间8点30或东部时间9点30前
and anyone not in their homes 8:30 central time,

433
00:26:43,100 --> 00:26:44,340
还没回家的人
or 9:30...

434
00:26:44,340 --> 00:26:47,940
费城5点的一波  我们应该赢定了
Five o'clock wave from Philly. I think we're home.

435
00:26:47,940 --> 00:26:50,730
...被拘禁甚至逮捕  这则公告...
...detention and possible arrest. This announcement...

436
00:26:57,100 --> 00:26:59,050
田纳西的事简直疯了
That Tennessee shit is crazy.

437
00:27:00,670 --> 00:27:02,140
疯狂事经常有
Crazy shit happens all the time.

438
00:27:02,670 --> 00:27:03,910
这么凑巧
This convenient?

439
00:27:06,260 --> 00:27:08,090
少来什么阴谋论了
Spare me the conspiracy talk.

440
00:27:08,500 --> 00:27:11,760
政府没那么大威力  或能力
The government's not that powerful... or competent.

441
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:15,340
总得问问
A man can ask.

442
00:27:22,180 --> 00:27:25,070
目前安德伍德255  康威245
We're looking at 255 Underwood, 245 Conway.

443
00:27:25,070 --> 00:27:26,540
宾州和俄亥俄呢
Pennsylvania and Ohio?

444
00:27:26,540 --> 00:27:28,980
还是太接近  但就要6点了
Still too close, but it's almost six o' clock.

445
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:32,130
等我们把田纳西州从康威变成摇摆
When we change Tennessee from Conway to undecided--

446
00:27:32,130 --> 00:27:32,780
那么康威会下跌
That brings Conway down

447
00:27:32,780 --> 00:27:34,660
-到...  -234  还是太接近
- to-- - Two thirty-four. Still way too close.

448
00:27:34,660 --> 00:27:35,700
是啊  我们尚不知道
Yes, but we don't yet know

449
00:27:35,710 --> 00:27:37,180
他已经拿下了西部州
that he's locked in the western states.

450
00:27:37,180 --> 00:27:39,100
那些州十年没变了
Those states have been locked up for ten years.

451
00:27:39,100 --> 00:27:42,610
红的  红的  红的  到今晚结束又会是红的
Red, red, red and they'll be red again by the end of the night.

452
00:27:42,610 --> 00:27:44,630
就看宾州和俄亥俄了
It's gonna come down to Pennsylvania and Ohio.

453
00:27:44,640 --> 00:27:47,240
康威需要两个州  你只需要一个
Conway needs both. You only need one.

454
00:27:47,810 --> 00:27:48,960
马修斯
Matthews?

455
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:51,190
他会反抗  可能还会公开表态
He'll push back. He might even go public.

456
00:27:51,790 --> 00:27:53,500
另外五个州呢
What about the other five states in play?

457
00:27:53,500 --> 00:27:54,450
律师在候着
The lawyers are waiting.

458
00:27:54,450 --> 00:27:56,970
我们可以就压制投票提出诉讼  但是
We can generate lawsuits, argue suppression, but...

459
00:27:56,970 --> 00:27:58,200
还是不够
Still not enough.

460
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:02,480
奥姆斯泰德在俄亥俄情况不乐观  他很不高兴
Olmstead's losing in Ohio, and he's not taking it well.

461
00:28:02,480 --> 00:28:04,410
我今早跟他的幕僚长塔妮娅通过话
I spoke with his chief of staff, Tanya, this morning.

462
00:28:04,410 --> 00:28:06,310
他在州北的情况很糟
He's getting clobbered in the northern part of the state.

463
00:28:06,310 --> 00:28:07,740
克利夫兰的低投票率也是个问题
Low turnout in Cleveland's not helping.

464
00:28:07,740 --> 00:28:09,180
但他还能扭转局势
But he could still pull it out.

465
00:28:09,180 --> 00:28:12,010
他赢不了的  他也清楚
He's not going to win and he knows it.

466
00:28:13,010 --> 00:28:14,520
我们还有多少时间
How much time do we have?

467
00:28:14,520 --> 00:28:18,280
俄亥俄州两小时后关闭  大部分人今早都投票了
Ohio closes in two hours. And most people voted this morning.

468
00:28:18,620 --> 00:28:20,560
有些州局势已定了
Some of these states are baked in already.

469
00:28:24,730 --> 00:28:26,950
克莱尔和我要单独谈谈
Claire and I need the room for a moment.

470
00:28:27,480 --> 00:28:28,360
是  先生
Yes, sir.

471
00:28:28,620 --> 00:28:30,850
-莉安  我们再联络你  -是  先生
- LeAnn, we'll call you back. - Yes, sir.

472
00:28:42,270 --> 00:28:43,880
你为什么让他出去
Why did you ask him to leave?

473
00:28:47,110 --> 00:28:51,910
因为我想再看着你的眼睛一次
Because I just wanted to look in your eyes one more time

474
00:28:51,910 --> 00:28:53,690
再决定要不要动手
before we do this.

475
00:28:55,770 --> 00:28:56,890
弗兰西斯
Francis...

476
00:28:57,560 --> 00:28:58,890
我们做吧
we're doing this.

477
00:29:07,490 --> 00:29:10,910
他救不了我们  他发明了任期限制
He can't save us. He invented term limits.

478
00:29:13,410 --> 00:29:14,270
道格
Doug!

479
00:29:16,940 --> 00:29:18,870
再给我接莉安·哈维
Get me LeAnn Harvey back on the phone.

480
00:29:20,130 --> 00:29:21,040
是  先生
Yes, sir.

481
00:29:21,160 --> 00:29:23,020
对俄亥俄做该做的吧
Do what you have to do with Ohio.

482
00:29:23,030 --> 00:29:23,930
我就去
I'm on it.

483
00:29:25,510 --> 00:29:28,070
莉安  让律师准备
LeAnn, get the lawyers ready.

484
00:29:30,100 --> 00:29:32,050
-我不能这么做  -你可以的
- I can't do this. - Yes, you can.

485
00:29:32,050 --> 00:29:35,210
-不不  -而且得马上完成
- No, no, no, no, no! - And it needs to be done quickly.

486
00:29:35,210 --> 00:29:37,190
太草率了
It's too sloppy.

487
00:29:37,190 --> 00:29:38,930
是莉安打的电话  为什么是你来
Why are you here if LeAnn called me?

488
00:29:38,930 --> 00:29:40,180
我还要向你解释
Do I really have to explain to you

489
00:29:40,180 --> 00:29:41,750
你不这么做的后果吗
what will happen if you don't do this?

490
00:29:41,750 --> 00:29:44,580
我不在乎他输不输
I don't care if he loses.

491
00:29:44,580 --> 00:29:48,170
我不是指选举  我是说你
I'm not talking about the election. I'm talking about you.

492
00:29:48,460 --> 00:29:50,630
你会怎么样
What will happen to you?

493
00:29:53,050 --> 00:29:56,330
你有你需要的一切了  链接已经发给你了
You have everything you need. The Pastebin link was sent to you.

494
00:30:00,560 --> 00:30:01,450
莉安呢
Where's LeAnn?

495
00:30:01,450 --> 00:30:03,550
她不在  我时间不多了
She's not here, and I'm short on time.

496
00:30:30,390 --> 00:30:33,450
州长  对不起  但这事只有一个办法
Governor, I'm sorry, but there's only one way to play this.

497
00:30:33,450 --> 00:30:34,770
我们需要你撤掉那三郡的
We need you to pull your poll workers

498
00:30:34,770 --> 00:30:36,270
投票工作人员和投票机
and your machines from those three counties.

499
00:30:36,270 --> 00:30:38,560
共和党人会宰了我的  那是他们的地盘
The Republicans would crucify me. They own that area.

500
00:30:38,570 --> 00:30:39,610
但那几个选区
But those are the precincts

501
00:30:39,610 --> 00:30:41,820
最有可能遭遇威胁
that are most likely to be threatened.

502
00:30:41,820 --> 00:30:44,200
"可能"  你什么...
"Likely to be"? Hey, what are you...

503
00:30:44,200 --> 00:30:45,720
这是什么意思
What are we talking about here?

504
00:30:46,180 --> 00:30:47,490
恐怖袭击可能性
Terrorist chatter.

505
00:30:47,500 --> 00:30:48,940
针对田纳西州的
Related to Tennessee?

506
00:30:49,170 --> 00:30:50,040
是的
Yes, sir.

507
00:30:50,040 --> 00:30:51,660
我可不能光听你空口一词
Well, I'm gonna need more than your word on that.

508
00:30:51,660 --> 00:30:54,340
对不起  但情报是机密  州长
Oh, I'm sorry, but the intelligence is classified, Governor.

509
00:30:54,340 --> 00:30:55,910
那给我权限
Then read me in.

510
00:30:56,180 --> 00:30:56,810
我没亲眼
'Cause I'm not doing this

511
00:30:56,810 --> 00:30:58,860
看到证据是不会这么做的
without seeing tangible proof with my own eyes.

512
00:30:58,860 --> 00:31:00,020
你去告诉弗兰西斯吧
You can tell Francis.

513
00:31:00,020 --> 00:31:02,830
另外  因为俄亥俄州投票率这么低
The other thing is, with Ohio turnout so low,

514
00:31:02,940 --> 00:31:05,790
可能会有人指控你刻意压制投票
people could accuse you of engaging in voter suppression.

515
00:31:05,790 --> 00:31:06,710
什么
What?

516
00:31:06,730 --> 00:31:10,490
投票中心和警卫队都是总统的主意
The voting centers and the troops were the president's idea.

517
00:31:10,490 --> 00:31:12,010
但你同意了
But you signed on to them,

518
00:31:12,230 --> 00:31:13,610
这才重要
and that's what matters.

519
00:31:13,750 --> 00:31:15,500
你要输掉选举了  先生
You're losing your election, sir.

520
00:31:15,500 --> 00:31:16,810
这很明显
The signs are clear.

521
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:19,880
民主党失去一位州长就太可惜了
That'd be a real shame for the Democrats to be down a governor.

522
00:31:19,880 --> 00:31:22,570
但现在发生了种种情况
But here we have this confluence of events.

523
00:31:23,030 --> 00:31:25,860
一方面是你不尽如人意的选情
Your disappointing returns on one hand

524
00:31:25,950 --> 00:31:27,520
一方面是恐怖袭击的可能
and the chatter on the other.

525
00:31:28,070 --> 00:31:30,660
我需要证据  否则  人们会觉得
I need proof. Otherwise, people will think--

526
00:31:30,660 --> 00:31:33,530
你为了赢得选举  而关闭了
That you shut down voting in Republican precincts

527
00:31:33,530 --> 00:31:35,450
共和党选区的投票站
to guarantee your own win.

528
00:31:35,460 --> 00:31:36,730
幸好
Now I'd say it's a good thing

529
00:31:36,730 --> 00:31:39,330
国安局刚收到了可靠的消息
that the NSA just picked up on some credible chatter.

530
00:31:39,960 --> 00:31:42,230
这危险的世界让你别无选择
This dangerous world left you no choice.

531
00:31:45,470 --> 00:31:46,490
谢谢
Thank you.

532
00:31:47,410 --> 00:31:51,330
州长  我刚刚拿到了机密情报
Governor, I was just handed the classified intel.

533
00:31:52,240 --> 00:31:53,760
您在加密服务器上吗
Are you on a secure server?

534
00:31:53,770 --> 00:31:55,980
-在  -请稍等
- Yes, I am. - Please hold.

535
00:32:00,840 --> 00:32:02,780
我这就把文件发给您
I'm sending the files over right now.

536
00:32:04,870 --> 00:32:07,210
{\pos(312.9,252)}取消           发送

537
00:32:18,050 --> 00:32:19,690
您的决定是正确的  先生
You're doing the right thing, sir.

538
00:32:19,760 --> 00:32:21,550
我们可不能背上血债
We don't want blood on our hands.

539
00:32:23,890 --> 00:32:26,610
我不管他们把投票机搬哪去
I don't care where they're taking the voting machines.

540
00:32:26,620 --> 00:32:27,560
你就盯紧...
Just stay...

541
00:32:27,780 --> 00:32:30,060
有必要的话把你自己绑在投票机上
You chain yourself to one of them if you have to.

542
00:32:30,690 --> 00:32:32,750
好  我去找个俄亥俄州的法官
Good. I'm gonna find an Ohio judge.

543
00:32:33,300 --> 00:32:36,060
俄亥俄州的投票中心已经关了近两个小时了
Voting centers in Ohio have been closed for almost two hours.

544
00:32:36,060 --> 00:32:37,260
康威已经去找法官了
And Conway's got a judge.

545
00:32:37,260 --> 00:32:38,640
他在申请重开投票中心
He's petitioning to reopen.

546
00:32:38,640 --> 00:32:40,250
但就算投票中心继续关闭
But even if they stay closed,

547
00:32:40,250 --> 00:32:41,500
俄亥俄州能帮我们达成目的吗
would Ohio get us there?

548
00:32:41,500 --> 00:32:43,220
其他州可能还有戏
Other states might be in play.

549
00:32:43,220 --> 00:32:45,570
压制投票的传言也出现了  但...
Rumblings of suppression are out there, although...

550
00:32:45,570 --> 00:32:46,610
还有什么别的情况
Well, what else do we have?

551
00:32:46,610 --> 00:32:48,250
爱达荷州  出现恐吓选民的事件
Voter intimidation in Idaho.

552
00:32:48,260 --> 00:32:50,700
怎么样  我要不要回话让他们提交诉讼
What do you think? Should I call them back and have them file?

553
00:32:50,780 --> 00:32:51,740
我看行
I like it.

554
00:32:52,130 --> 00:32:54,750
这样和田纳西的事呼应效果最好
It has the most resonance with what's happened in Tennessee.

555
00:32:54,750 --> 00:32:57,330
我还希望佐治亚有议员站出来
I also like an assemblyman we have in Georgia.

556
00:32:57,330 --> 00:32:58,670
马里兰有个众议员
There's a congressman in Maryland.

557
00:32:58,670 --> 00:33:01,090
马里兰也是没要求派警卫队的州之一
That's one of the states that didn't request the troops.

558
00:33:01,090 --> 00:33:03,250
等等  我们需不需要普通选民出来表态
But wait. Don't we need something coming from a voter?

559
00:33:03,260 --> 00:33:04,810
密西西比有个选民
There's a voter in Mississippi.

560
00:33:04,820 --> 00:33:06,570
她说她吓得不敢去投票了
Said she was too scared to vote.

561
00:33:06,570 --> 00:33:08,730
新闻基本就是告诉她不要去投票
That TV essentially told her not to go.

562
00:33:08,730 --> 00:33:10,650
这就有点牵强了吧
Well, that sounds like a bit of a stretch.

563
00:33:10,650 --> 00:33:13,070
可能对我们有利  先生
That could be a plus for us, sir.

564
00:33:13,080 --> 00:33:14,580
能很好地打开局面
Really open things up.

565
00:33:14,580 --> 00:33:16,270
如果俄亥俄继续关闭
If Ohio stays shut,

566
00:33:16,270 --> 00:33:17,740
可能会引发连锁反应
there could be a ripple effect.

567
00:33:17,740 --> 00:33:19,820
这都是前无古人的做法
This is all uncharted territory.

568
00:33:19,820 --> 00:33:21,960
那好  佐治亚和马里兰待会儿再说
All right, let's put a pin in Georgia and Maryland,

569
00:33:21,960 --> 00:33:24,500
让俄亥俄的投票中心继续关闭
and let's keep the Ohio voting centers shut down,

570
00:33:24,500 --> 00:33:26,190
看看有什么结果
and see where that gets us.

571
00:33:26,190 --> 00:33:28,920
康威已经拿下宾夕法尼亚
Pennsylvania has gone to Conway.

572
00:33:26,200 --> 00:33:31,710
{\an1}康威拿下宾夕法尼亚

573
00:33:28,930 --> 00:33:32,090
就算双方在俄亥俄仍然难分胜负
Even if Ohio is still too close to call

574
00:33:32,090 --> 00:33:34,620
总统在西北部取胜的话
and the President does well in the Northwest,

575
00:33:34,830 --> 00:33:37,600
他仍无法抵消康威在南部取得的优势
he can't counter Conway's gains in the South,

576
00:33:37,600 --> 00:33:40,110
而那里曾是安德伍德的地盘
in what would typically be Underwood territory.

577
00:33:40,110 --> 00:33:41,870
人民已经做出了选择
The people have spoken.

578
00:33:43,050 --> 00:33:44,580
真是难以置信
I can't believe this.

579
00:33:44,580 --> 00:33:47,090
总统因故不能前来  他向各位表示歉意
The President apologizes that he couldn't be here tonight,

580
00:33:47,520 --> 00:33:51,200
但他想让我告诉各位  败选已经不可避免了
but he wanted me to let you know that concession is inevitable.

581
00:33:51,850 --> 00:33:53,750
还有那么多州票没计完
All the states haven't been called yet.

582
00:33:53,750 --> 00:33:55,410
总统还有时间想办法...
The president still has time if he needs...

583
00:33:55,410 --> 00:33:57,860
各位  我们已经尽力了
Guys, we fought a good fight.

584
00:33:57,860 --> 00:34:01,000
可是很不幸  实情就是这样
But, unfortunately, this is the reality of the situation.

585
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:02,290
天啊
Jesus.

586
00:34:04,580 --> 00:34:06,030
看来这就算完了
Well, I guess that's that.

587
00:34:11,190 --> 00:34:12,060
喂  我是威尔
Yeah, this is Will.

588
00:34:12,060 --> 00:34:13,850
我想第一个对你说
I wanted to be the first to tell you

589
00:34:13,850 --> 00:34:17,040
恭喜你  当选总统先生
congratulations, Mr. President-elect.

590
00:34:18,130 --> 00:34:20,130
谢谢你  总统先生
Well, thank you, Mr. President.

591
00:34:20,460 --> 00:34:22,880
{\an3}{\pos(374,247)}2000年大选夜  戈尔先向小布什认输
但是第二天又反悔了

592
00:34:20,460 --> 00:34:22,880
怎么  你以为我没从戈尔那里学到教训吗
What? You think I learned nothing from Al Gore?

593
00:34:24,570 --> 00:34:27,070
我们这场选战可真是激烈万分啊  是不是
We kept them on the edge of their seats, didn't we?

594
00:34:28,760 --> 00:34:31,110
我想这也说明我们的体制运转良好
I guess that means the system is working.

595
00:34:31,110 --> 00:34:32,640
我也这么看
I guess it does.

596
00:34:32,640 --> 00:34:34,970
你是我遇到过的最强劲的对手了  弗兰西斯
You're about as tough an opponent as they come, Francis.

597
00:34:34,970 --> 00:34:36,910
我经验丰富啊
Well, I've had a lot of practice.

598
00:34:36,910 --> 00:34:39,900
请一定要转达我对汉娜和孩子们的问候
Now, you be sure to give my regards to Hannah and the children.

599
00:34:39,900 --> 00:34:41,730
谢谢你  总统先生  我
Thank you, Mr. President. I'm...

600
00:34:42,550 --> 00:34:45,530
我在不久的将来  肯定会向你讨教的
sure I'll be calling on you for advice in the very near future.

601
00:34:45,530 --> 00:34:47,390
我万分期待
Well, I look forward to that.

602
00:34:58,210 --> 00:34:59,570
他认输了
He conceded?

603
00:35:05,290 --> 00:35:06,210
对
Yeah.

604
00:35:11,220 --> 00:35:12,120
我们成功了
We did it.

605
00:35:14,260 --> 00:35:15,280
我们做到了
We did it.

606
00:35:16,230 --> 00:35:17,490
打扰一下  先生
Excuse me, sir.

607
00:35:18,300 --> 00:35:20,620
布洛哈特将军正在来套房的路上
General Brockhart is on his way over to the suite.

608
00:35:20,710 --> 00:35:21,630
谢谢
Thank you.

609
00:35:29,700 --> 00:35:36,790
{\an7}安德伍德总统是否已认输

610
00:35:29,810 --> 00:35:31,790
有消息源称  不久前
Sources are telling us that Francis Underwood

611
00:35:31,790 --> 00:35:34,030
弗兰西斯·安德伍德致电康威州长
conceded to Governor Conway on the phone

612
00:35:34,030 --> 00:35:35,830
承认落选
only a short time ago.

613
00:35:35,830 --> 00:35:38,650
我猜测他们收到的数字跟我们的相符
I suspect their numbers are matching up with ours,

614
00:35:36,790 --> 00:35:46,260
{\an7}安德伍德总统是否已认输

615
00:35:38,650 --> 00:35:41,610
那么俄亥俄将被共和党收入囊中
which would put Ohio in the Republican column.

616
00:35:41,610 --> 00:35:43,220
足以让威廉·康威
Enough to make William Conway

617
00:35:43,220 --> 00:35:46,100
成为美国下一任总统
the next president of the United States.

618
00:35:54,660 --> 00:35:56,220
-你好  -塔妮娅  让他接电话
- Hello? - Tanya, put him on the line.

619
00:35:56,220 --> 00:35:57,680
等一下  我看看能不能找到他
Hang on, let me see if I can get him.

620
00:35:57,690 --> 00:35:59,000
他是我的州务卿
He's my Secretary of State,

621
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:00,320
他有权这么做
and he has the power to do it.

622
00:36:00,320 --> 00:36:02,080
那你得告诉他该做什么
Well, then you need to tell him what to do.

623
00:36:02,080 --> 00:36:04,700
他说他可以重开选站将投票日延长到明天
He says he can reopen and extend the voting day into tomorrow.

624
00:36:04,700 --> 00:36:05,940
告诉他这不安全
Tell him it's not safe.

625
00:36:05,950 --> 00:36:07,010
我说了  道格
I've done that, Doug!

626
00:36:07,010 --> 00:36:08,610
他显然不在乎
Obviously, he doesn't seem to care.

627
00:36:08,620 --> 00:36:10,590
安德伍德已经认输了
Underwood conceded already.

628
00:36:10,590 --> 00:36:14,030
别放你的州务卿出去
Do not trot out your Secretary of State.

629
00:36:14,220 --> 00:36:15,250
投票不能重启
Voting cannot resume.

630
00:36:15,250 --> 00:36:16,160
如果你还有什么疑虑
Now, if you have any doubt,

631
00:36:16,160 --> 00:36:17,800
那也给我忍着
you swallow it right now.

632
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:18,890
我担心的是党派
I'm worried about the party.

633
00:36:18,890 --> 00:36:20,120
这对党派的影响
What this could do to the party.

634
00:36:20,120 --> 00:36:22,520
罗杰  这比党派重要多了
Roger, this is so much bigger than the party.

635
00:36:23,420 --> 00:36:25,390
我觉得我把我的事业都赌上了
I feel like I'm risking my entire career here.

636
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:26,400
是的
You are.

637
00:36:26,930 --> 00:36:29,030
如果你不照我说的做
And if you don't do what I'm telling you,

638
00:36:29,040 --> 00:36:30,500
你的前途就完了
it's over for sure.

639
00:36:36,290 --> 00:36:37,180
怎么了
What?

640
00:36:44,580 --> 00:36:45,860
他还要耗多久
How many hours is it gonna take him

641
00:36:45,860 --> 00:36:48,020
才肯在公众面前说出那几个字
to spit out the fucking words in public?

642
00:36:48,330 --> 00:36:49,550
不管了  去他的规程
Screw this. Screw protocol.

643
00:36:49,550 --> 00:36:50,530
我这就要过去
I'm heading down there.

644
00:36:50,540 --> 00:36:52,040
-不  不行  -已经到第二天了  马克
- No, you're not. - It's already tomorrow, Mark.

645
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:53,220
这简直不可理喻
I mean, this is insane.

646
00:36:53,220 --> 00:36:56,060
-我想发表讲话  -俄亥俄州还没完
- I want to make my speech! - Ohio is still in play.

647
00:36:56,290 --> 00:36:57,190
什么
What?

648
00:36:58,990 --> 00:37:00,120
你在说什么
What are you talking about?

649
00:37:00,720 --> 00:37:03,070
持续的恐怖主义威胁带来的恐慌...
...fear from continued terrorist threats

650
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:05,690
和田纳西州传出的令人不安的消息
and the disturbing news coming out of Tennessee...

651
00:37:07,700 --> 00:37:10,930
让我不得不关闭几个我们的投票站
I was forced to close a number of our polling places.

652
00:37:14,610 --> 00:37:16,820
操
Fuck me.

653
00:37:18,820 --> 00:37:21,720
经与俄亥俄州州务卿达成一致
And in accordance with the Ohio secretary of state,

654
00:37:21,930 --> 00:37:24,810
投票在进一步通知前先行暂停
the vote is suspended until further notice.

655
00:37:28,550 --> 00:37:31,060
我知道这会让我们的选民疑虑重重
Now, I know this may put our electorates in question...

656
00:37:32,640 --> 00:37:34,140
但我别无选择
...but I had no choice.

657
00:37:37,890 --> 00:37:39,420
新泽西可能不认证
New Jersey might not certify.

658
00:37:39,420 --> 00:37:41,630
出现了一些异常情况
There's been a variety of irregularities.

659
00:37:41,760 --> 00:37:43,280
伊利诺伊也是
Same with Illinois.

660
00:37:43,320 --> 00:37:45,890
看起来内华达也有异动
Looks like Nevada's making noises, too.

661
00:37:48,580 --> 00:37:52,080
感觉似曾相识  你有同感吗
I'm having déjà vu. You ever get that?

662
00:37:53,880 --> 00:37:56,150
你真的在问我似曾相识的感觉吗
Are you seriously asking me about déjà vu?

663
00:37:56,150 --> 00:37:58,020
算了  已经没感觉了
Never mind. It's gone.

664
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:02,440
你从未有过似曾相识的感觉吗  人人都会有
You never get déjà vu? Everybody does.

665
00:38:02,440 --> 00:38:03,450
我没有
I don't.

666
00:38:04,960 --> 00:38:06,660
别那么焦虑  道格
Don't look so worried, Doug.

667
00:38:06,670 --> 00:38:08,600
你就是那一瞬间感觉很熟悉
You just felt familiar for a second.

668
00:38:09,550 --> 00:38:10,430
已经过去了
It's over.

669
00:38:11,340 --> 00:38:14,040
现在  总统选举结果未定
Now, the presidency hangs in the balance.

670
00:38:13,240 --> 00:38:15,490
{\an1}部分州不能认证结果

671
00:38:14,040 --> 00:38:16,790
至少六个州将不能在2016的选举夜
At least six states will not have certified vote totals

672
00:38:15,490 --> 00:38:19,160
{\an1}部分州不能认证结果

673
00:38:16,790 --> 00:38:18,920
认证计票结果
on Election Night 2016.

674
00:38:21,060 --> 00:38:22,130
晚上好
Good evening.

675
00:38:23,740 --> 00:38:25,450
我猜我该说早上好
I guess I should say good morning.

676
00:38:28,920 --> 00:38:31,420
威尔很希望他能亲自出镜
Will wishes he could be here himself...

677
00:38:32,150 --> 00:38:34,730
但我们获知那有违规章
but we've been advised that goes against protocol.

678
00:38:36,010 --> 00:38:37,000
我知道...
I know...

679
00:38:38,440 --> 00:38:39,830
你们很失望
you're disappointed.

680
00:38:41,490 --> 00:38:43,220
你介意用失望这个词吗
Are you okay with the word disappointed?

681
00:38:46,350 --> 00:38:48,310
我们不该提到他们的愤怒吗
Shouldn't we acknowledge their outrage?

682
00:38:48,310 --> 00:38:50,090
我觉得我们应该小心处理
I'd say we should tread lightly.

683
00:38:50,140 --> 00:38:52,630
目前我们只想请他们保持耐心
For now, we're just asking for their patience.

684
00:38:52,630 --> 00:38:54,460
好  我们拍吧
Okay, let's do it.

685
00:38:55,700 --> 00:38:56,950
{\an1}汉娜·康威就结果发表讲话

686
00:38:55,810 --> 00:38:58,120
这个国家就没有无聊的时候
Never a dull moment in this country.

687
00:38:56,950 --> 00:38:59,120
{\an1}汉娜·康威就结果发表讲话

688
00:38:59,580 --> 00:39:01,760
威尔很希望他能亲自出镜
Will wishes he could be here himself,

689
00:39:01,760 --> 00:39:05,620
但我们获知那有违规章
but we've been advised that would go against protocol.

690
00:39:05,890 --> 00:39:08,330
我知道你们很失望
I know you're disappointed

691
00:39:08,330 --> 00:39:11,100
你们所期待的改变
that the change you were hoping for...

692
00:39:11,150 --> 00:39:12,520
你们所投票支持的改变
...that you voted for,

693
00:39:12,520 --> 00:39:14,640
得再等一段时间
has to wait a little longer.

694
00:39:20,140 --> 00:39:23,190
{\an1}{\pos(147,242.1)}{\an7} 艾·麦卡伦莉  我受不了了  对不起  麦卡...

695
00:39:32,330 --> 00:39:35,240
最终  这没有定论的选举之夜
And, finally, a night of electoral indecision,

696
00:39:33,240 --> 00:39:35,330
{\an1}大选之夜的混乱

697
00:39:35,240 --> 00:39:37,920
几乎每个州都提起了诉讼
with lawsuits being filed in nearly every state,

698
00:39:37,920 --> 00:39:40,000
为它画上句号的是檀香山市长
has ended with the mayor of Honolulu,

699
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:42,260
最后一个关闭了投票
in the last state to close its polls,

700
00:39:42,260 --> 00:39:44,940
并拒绝承认选举结果
refusing to honor the results of the election

701
00:39:44,940 --> 00:39:46,610
还提起了诉讼
and filing a lawsuit.

702
00:39:46,820 --> 00:39:48,100
夏威夷是我们这边的吗
Was Hawaii one of ours?

703
00:39:48,110 --> 00:39:49,950
应该不是
No, I don't think so.

704
00:39:54,350 --> 00:39:56,690
克莱尔  能帮我个忙吗
Claire, could you do me a little favor?

705
00:39:57,240 --> 00:39:58,530
我头很痛
I have a splitting headache.

706
00:39:58,530 --> 00:40:01,230
你能揉揉我的太阳穴吗
Could you rub my temples for a moment?

707
00:40:02,200 --> 00:40:03,270
当然
Of course.

708
00:40:07,420 --> 00:40:10,280
不  其实是我眼睛这里疼
No, actually the pain is right behind my eyes.

709
00:40:10,280 --> 00:40:14,100
你能...给我揉揉眼睛吗
Could you just... rub my eyes for me?

710
00:40:14,890 --> 00:40:16,370
但是你讨厌那样
But you hate that.

711
00:40:16,860 --> 00:40:19,480
我知道  但是这次我应该会喜欢
